2.2.2. Flagged records

The anthropometric z-scores are calculated using the {zscorer}. Values are then assessed based on the WHO flagging criteria and problematic values are flagged. For this, we only use the data from children 6-59 months old and we first calculate z-score using the first measurements.

This produces an updated anthropometric dataset that now includes calculated anthropometric z-scores (weight-for-age, height-for-age, and weight-for-height) and identifies flagged values based on WHO flagging criteria and indicates which anthropometric measurement is potentially problematic.

2.2.7. Sex ratio

The sex ratio in the anthropometric dataset is compared against the expected sex ratio of children under 5 years old in Mozambique which is 1.03 males for every female (from the United States Census Bureau’s International Data Base).

## 
##  Sex Ratio Test
## 
## Expected proportion male = 0.5074
## Observed proportion male = 0.5238
## X-squared = 0.9322, p = 0.3343

The ratio of boys and girls in the data is not significantly different from the ratio of boys and girls in the general population in Mozambique.
